# Tooling Conventions

## Package Management — uv

```powershell
# ✅ Add a dependency
uv add fastapi

# ✅ Add a dev dependency
uv add --dev pytest pytest-asyncio

# ✅ Install all dependencies
uv sync --all-extras

# ✅ Run a script/command in the project environment
uv run pytest
uv run uvicorn src.main:app --reload

# ❌ NEVER use pip directly
pip install fastapi
```

All dependencies must be declared in `pyproject.toml`. The `uv.lock` file must be committed.

## Code Quality — ruff

ruff handles **everything**: linting, formatting, import sorting.
Never configure black, isort, or flake8 separately.

```powershell
# Check for issues (with auto-fix where safe)
uv run ruff check . --fix

# Format code
uv run ruff format .

# Both at once (CI order)
uv run ruff check . && uv run ruff format --check .
```

Configuration lives in `pyproject.toml [tool.ruff]` — do not create `.ruff.toml`.

## Testing — pytest

```powershell
# Run all tests
uv run pytest

# Run specific module
uv run pytest tests/unit/modules/search/

# Run with coverage
uv run pytest --cov=src --cov-report=term-missing
```

- `asyncio_mode = "auto"` is set in `pyproject.toml` — no need for `@pytest.mark.asyncio`
- Async test functions work out of the box: `async def test_something(): ...`
